FromWeb?topicID=1650.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some help on healing strategies needed...</span><hr size=1>    Keep them alive :-o  Just kiddin.  Up until around lvl 70-75 MAs are decent healers in groups and can do a fair substitution job for a doc.  Just keep your bio and sense as high as possible (maxed ideally) and well implanted.  The way I heal depends on the type of MOBs were fighting.  If, say, 90% of the time there's only one person being attacked (the tank), then I single heal that person just because those heals are stronger.  On the other hand, if there is some likelihood of multiple people gettin pounded on I'll just chain team heal.  Team heals also cast slightly faster so take that into consideration.<br>   Also, if you are the primary (or only) healer in the group I wouldn't get involved in combat unless your group is just ripping through the mobs.  You need to keep aggro off of you so you can pop nano kits and if you attack you have a very high chance of getting attacked since we're low damage, pesky annoyances =p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uautumndawnfire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Autumn Dawnfire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.melanierawn.com/images/bunnie.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#660000>(2/12/02 10:59:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1650.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some help on healing strategies needed...</span><hr size=1> I'd say choosing to get into combat when prime healers will largely depend on the skill level of your other tanks, especially enforcers.  If you enforcer knows how to control agg, you're damage can do help on your heals ( dead npc's don't do damage ).   But keep in mind that healing is only a portion of healing for a group, as a MA you can reduce damage taken by the group also, in two ways.<br><br>By making sure you get your group the best ac buffs you carry, and the best evades you carry you can mitigate the damage they take, making your job as a healer a bit easier.<br><br>By increasing offensive ability of your group you again make your job easy because the npc's die faster and tax your healing ability less.  That's not *just* the crit hit lines, that's throwing the MA+ programs on folks using MA as their weapon, that's making sure everyone on your team that brawls have Dirty Fighter, if they have space for even throw on a Muscle Stim ( it doesn't hurt to do so ).  The only thing you need to be careful of making sure your enforcers have space left for mongo if they need to use it.  Same goes for HoT's ( heal over time ) when you have a doc in group.<br><br>Keep in mind we do more for group support then just heal, a lot more.  If your team is having to ask you for buffs when timers run out, your not being efficient in your job.  Track your buff timers yourself, if  combat is heavy and you aren't going to have the luxury of stopping the fighting to get people rebuffed, start spacing it out and doing it every fight untill you have everyone rebuffed.<br><br>Watch those timers, you will reduce your ability to group alive if you aren't on top of your buff timers.  Buff timers are REALLY easy to track, execute on yourself FIRST, when yours are getting to around the 5 minute mark... start renewing, but hold nano to heal if you need to, don't empty your tank unless the group can stop fighting or if you are the back up healer of have another secondary healer there to pick up the slack while you rebuff the team.<br><br>But.. NEVER go empty even with another healer if haven't let them know what your doing first.<br><br>If you have a puller let them know you in rebuff cycle also,  good commnication is critcal at those times ( always really but hyper crititical when the puller is counting on the group doing X amount of damage and being able to heal X amount of damage - totally throws them off if they don't know you completely in the fight. <p><http://www.anarchy-online.com/character/photos/40240.jpg><BR>Tigerwhite<BR>"Tigerwhite burning bright"</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1650.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1650.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1650.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.emailToFriend?topicID=1650.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.threadControl?topicID=1650.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1650.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1650.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub83